data.enText: following one after another in a series, without interruption
She was absent for nine consecutive days.
He is beginning his fourth consecutive term of office.

simple_means.memory_skill: con 加强 + secut 跟随 + ive …的 → 一个跟一个 → 连贯的

value.def: Consecutive periods of time or events happen one after the other without interruption.

example.ex: The Cup was won for the third consecutive year by the Toronto Maple Leafs...
example.tran: 多伦多枫叶队连续第三年捧杯。

example.ex: Photographs taken at the same time on two consecutive sunny days can be quite different from one another.
example.tran: 在连续两个艳阳天的同一时间拍摄的照片也可能大不相同。

example.ex: ...a CD player which plays six CDs consecutively.
example.tran: 可以连续播放6张CD的CD播放机

trans: 交传；即席翻译；即席口译；交替传译；接续传译

partsOfSpeech.dec: con 加强 + secut 跟随 + ive …的 → 一个跟一个 → 连贯的
con 加强 + sequ 跟随 + ence 表行为 → 随后发生 → 后果
ob 加强 + sequ 跟随 + ious …的 → 拼命跟随的 → 谄媚的
per 加强 + secut 跟随 + e → 跟在后面〔坏你的事〕→ 迫害
per 加强 + secut 跟随 + ion 表名词 → 迫害
pro 在前 + secut 跟随 + e → 跟随〔法官〕在他面前〔告状〕→ 控告
sequ 跟随 + acious 多…的 → 跟风的 → 盲从的
sequ 跟随 + ence 表性质，状态 → 一个跟一个 → 连续
sequ 跟随 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 + ial …的 → 连续的
sub 接近 + sequ 跟随 + ence 性质，状态，行为 → 紧跟在后面 → 随后发生的事
